---
/**
 * About Page
 * Information about the blog with Discordian personality
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/common/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/common/Footer.astro';
import Card from '../components/ui/Card.astro';
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.astro';

const title = 'About 1001 Schr√∂dinger\'s Cats';
const description = 'A Discordian exploration of science, philosophy, life, the universe, and everything';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Header />

  <main class="main-content">
    <div class="container">
      <!-- Hero Section -->
      <section class="hero-section">
        <h1 class="page-title">
          About 1001 Schr√∂dinger's Cats
        </h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          A Discordian blog exploring the quantum superposition of existence
        </p>
        <div class="hero-icon">üçé</div>
      </section>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <section class="content-section">
        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">What is this place?</h2>
            <p>
              Welcome to <strong>1001 Schr√∂dinger's Cats</strong>, a blog that exists in a
              perpetual state of quantum superposition between profound insight and utter nonsense‚Äî
              until you observe it, at which point the wave function collapses into whichever
              you were expecting anyway.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is a space dedicated to exploring <strong>science</strong>, <strong>philosophy</strong>,
              <strong>technology</strong>, and the general absurdity of existence through the lens of
              Discordian philosophy. We embrace chaos, celebrate contradictions, and acknowledge that
              all statements (including this one) are true in some sense, false in some sense, and
              meaningless in some sense.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Card>

        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Law of Fives</h2>
            <p>
              You may notice that everything here comes in fives. This is not a coincidence because
              <em>nothing is a coincidence</em>. The Law of Fives states that all things happen in fives,
              or are divisible by or are multiples of five, or are somehow directly or indirectly
              appropriate to five.
            </p>
            <p>
              Therefore, you'll find:
            </p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>A maximum of 5 tags per post</li>
              <li>Exactly 5 recent posts on the homepage</li>
              <li>5 related posts shown after each article</li>
              <li>This list has exactly 5 items</li>
              <li>The number five appears 5 times in this list</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </Card>

        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">Topics We Explore</h2>
            <div class="topics-grid">
              <div class="topic-card">
                <span class="topic-icon">üî¨</span>
                <h3>Science</h3>
                <p>Quantum mechanics, cosmology, biology, and the scientific method‚Äîwith occasional detours into pseudoscience for comparison.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="topic-card">
                <span class="topic-icon">üß†</span>
                <h3>Philosophy</h3>
                <p>Epistemology, consciousness, ethics, existentialism, and why we're all just brains in vats (or are we?).</p>
              </div>
              <div class="topic-card">
                <span class="topic-icon">üíª</span>
                <h3>Technology</h3>
                <p>Programming, AI, the future, and how we're building either a utopia or our doom (spoiler: yes).</p>
              </div>
              <div class="topic-card">
                <span class="topic-icon">üçé</span>
                <h3>Discordianism</h3>
                <p>Chaos magic, Eris worship, the Sacred Chao, and the serious business of not taking things seriously.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="topic-card">
                <span class="topic-icon">üåå</span>
                <h3>Everything</h3>
                <p>Life, the universe, and everything else that doesn't fit neatly into categories (which is most things).</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </Card>

        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">The Time-Based Theme</h2>
            <p>
              This blog changes its color scheme based on your local time, creating a dynamic reading
              experience that flows with the natural rhythm of your day:
            </p>
            <ul class="theme-list">
              <li><strong>üåÖ Morning (6am-12pm):</strong> Soft, warm pastels to ease you into consciousness</li>
              <li><strong>‚òÄÔ∏è Afternoon (12pm-6pm):</strong> Bright, energetic colors for peak productivity</li>
              <li><strong>üåÜ Evening (6pm-10pm):</strong> Warm, muted tones for winding down</li>
              <li><strong>üåô Night (10pm-6am):</strong> Dark mode for the night owls and insomniacs</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Because if you're going to read about quantum superposition and the heat death of the
              universe, you might as well do it in aesthetically appropriate lighting.
            </p>
          </div>
        </Card>

        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content">
            <h2 class="section-heading">Who Writes This?</h2>
            <p>
              This blog is maintained by a collection of Schr√∂dinger's cats who are simultaneously
              alive and dead until you finish reading a post. We are all Popes in the Discordian
              Church, which means you are too. Congratulations on your ordination!
            </p>
            <p>
              The content oscillates between deeply researched technical articles and existential
              ramblings, often within the same paragraph. We believe in:
            </p>
            <ul class="belief-list">
              <li>The scientific method (but not scientism)</li>
              <li>Critical thinking (but not cynicism)</li>
              <li>Humor as a form of wisdom</li>
              <li>Embracing uncertainty and paradox</li>
              <li>That this list should have exactly five items</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </Card>

        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="about-content discordian-notice">
            <h2 class="section-heading">‚ö†Ô∏è Important Notice ‚ö†Ô∏è</h2>
            <p class="notice-text">
              All statements on this blog are true in some sense, false in some sense, meaningless
              in some sense, true and false in some sense, true and meaningless in some sense, false
              and meaningless in some sense, and true and false and meaningless in some sense.
            </p>
            <p class="notice-attribution">
              ‚Äî A Discordian Interpretation of the Principia Discordia
            </p>
          </div>
        </Card>
      </section>

      <!-- Call to Action -->
      <section class="cta-section">
        <Card padding="lg">
          <div class="cta-content">
            <h2>Join the Exploration</h2>
            <p>
              Ready to dive into the quantum foam of ideas? Start reading, or use the search to
              find topics that interest you.
            </p>
            <div class="cta-buttons">
              <Button href="/blog" variant="primary" size="lg">
                Read the Blog
              </Button>
              <Button href="/search" variant="secondary" size="lg">
                Search Posts
              </Button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </Card>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer Quote -->
      <section class="footer-quote">
        <blockquote>
          <p class="quote-text">
            "A Discordian is Prohibited of Believing what he reads."
          </p>
          <cite class="quote-author">‚Äî Principia Discordia</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .main-content {
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }

  /* Hero Section */
  .hero-section {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-primary), var(--accent-secondary));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .hero-icon {
    font-size: 5rem;
    animation: float 3s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes float {
    0%, 100% {
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
    50% {
      transform: translateY(-20px);
    }
  }

  /* Content Section */
  .content-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-content {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .about-content strong {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Lists */
  .feature-list,
  .theme-list,
  .belief-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .feature-list li,
  .theme-list li,
  .belief-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0.75rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .feature-list li::before,
  .theme-list li::before,
  .belief-list li::before {
    content: 'üçé';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Topics Grid */
  .topics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .topic-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .topic-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-primary);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px var(--shadow-color);
  }

  .topic-icon {
    font-size: 3rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .topic-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .topic-card p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Discordian Notice */
  .discordian-notice {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 140, 0, 0.1), rgba(255, 69, 0, 0.1));
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-primary);
  }

  .notice-text {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .notice-attribution {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-content {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta-content p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* Footer Quote */
  .footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .footer-quote blockquote {
    border-left: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .quote-text {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .quote-author {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .main-content {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .hero-section {
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .hero-icon {
      font-size: 3rem;
    }

    .section-heading {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .about-content p,
    .feature-list li,
    .theme-list li,
    .belief-list li {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .topics-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cta-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .quote-text {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }

  /* Accessibility: Respect reduced motion */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .hero-icon {
      animation: none;
    }

    .topic-card {
      transition: none;
    }

    .topic-card:hover {
      transform: none;
    }
  }
</style>
